Author: DoggyDish
Text: If you can get a can opener than I recommend canned goods. Canned ravioli keeps one full for a long time and isn't bad at room temp. Fruit cocktail is also good.

Author: ExtremeCarob
Text: Definitely go to a local food pantry, ASAP. Look for non perishables like granola bars and other cereals for a quick was to get an easy 200-300 cals and is easy enough on the digestive system that you can take it on an empty stomach and then have your meds with water.   Nuts would also be good because that will round out your fats and proteins instead of just the big carb hit from the granola.
